## âš™ï¸ Installation & Setup

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.9+
- pip package manager
- Virtual environment (recommended)

### Step 1: Clone Repository

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/BharatTrend.git
cd BharatTrend

text

### Step 2: Create Virtual Environment

python -m venv venv

Windows
.\venv\Scripts\Activate

Linux/Mac
source venv/bin/activate

text

### Step 3: Install Dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt

text

### Step 4: Configure Settings

Edit `configs/config.yaml` with your preferences (subreddits, model settings, etc.)

---

## ğŸ® Usage

### Quick Start with Sample Data

1. Generate sample data
python src/data/create_sample_data.py

2. Clean data
python src/data/clean_data.py

3. Analyze sentiment
python src/features/sentiment_analyzer.py

4. Generate forecast
python src/models/train.py

5. Launch dashboard
streamlit run src/visualization/dashboard.py

text

### Using Real Data

**Reddit API Setup:**

1. Visit https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps
2. Create app and get credentials
3. Add to `.env` file:
REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=your_secret
REDDIT_USER_AGENT=BharatTrend/1.0

text

4. Run collection:
python src/data/collect_social.py

text

